10:
He will be born again elsewhere, in
another world, as dragons do.
15:
You were separated... from the
incarnate darkness... You will be fine
now...
19:
Hmph. Thou needst not fret over a
fool who tarnished the blood of
dragons.
24:
Couette, can I have the last bit of
the Curse Crystal?
29: What... are you going to use it for?
33:
...You were by my side this whole
time, right? Thank you for that,
Couette.
35:
I spent this whole time dreaming...
dreaming of a dragon's old memory.
39:
I can't remember what exactly I
dreamed about, but I know that
dragon was me.
46:
I'm Armadeus. So I'll become a
dragon.
50: B-but if you do that... Rooma will...
54: No... I don't want you to go! You can't!
58:
I know I'm being selfish! But I don't
care!
62:
Couette, I promise. I won't forget
you, no matter what.
67: That's not how it works! You know it!
73:
And the big bad pirate steals the
treasure! Here, I'll hand it over.
76:
Sorry, Couette, but a pirate does
what she wants.
84: Marina, it's okay... I'll do it...
88:
...I shouldn't have jumped the gun.
You're a strong girl, Couette.
93:
Serpent... open the way. Thou art...
art...
100:
Thank you, Couette. I swear I won't
break my promise.
104:
I'll remember you. I'll come find you
again!
117:
Where do you think you're going,
Edea?
120:
You won't get past me. Those
children are under my protection.
123:
It's been a long time, Luceltia. Or...
wait, it's Belsidia now, isn't it?
125:
By the way, I go by Capella now. This
is the first time you've seen this
body, isn't it?
128:
You should know that when I
change hosts, my mental processes
change too—personality,
preferences, et cetera.
131:
No, Edea. You haven't changed one
bit.
134:
Haha, coming from one who never
changes herself, I suppose I should
take your word for it.
137: I can take a hint. I'll take my leave.
139:
Goodbye, Sister. Be wary of the
curse of the sword.
144:
Whatever you're planning, I won't sit
around and hesitate any longer.
147:
Those children will be the ones to
push through the darkness, hand in
hand—
154:
This barren land gives nothing, but
takes all. Therefore, I have come to a
decision.
155:
I shall grant you the power of the
dragon. Drink my blood. Consume
my flesh.
156:
In return, I shall feast on your
dreams—
160: Hello, do you have a moment?
162:
You're a dragon too, aren't you? I
didn't expect to run into someone
else being reborn as well.
164:
Me? I'm Rustamov! A holy dragon!
Who are you?
186: Belsidia, what are you up to this time?
192:
Belsidia comes into my dreams a
lot. Which makes me think... Were
you helping this whole time?
196:
I'm afraid I did have to be sneaky. If I
made any moves on the other side,
Light would be pestering me left and
right!
199:
Not that he would be wrong to. I do
tend to teach you some naughty
things.
204:
Can you teach me about space and
the stars today?
208:
I want to know more about the sun,
the earth, and galaxies!
212:
I'm always happy to spoil you rotten,
but... what brought this on?
216:
I want to learn more about
everything. About this world... About
all the painful, scary things too...
219:
I have to catch up to Suizen and
surpass him in knowledge!
221: That way I can teach others...
224:
And show them all the beautiful and
fun things across every world!
